  "body": "# Rationale\r\n\r\nWhy should this feature \r\n* If this feature exists, we can fetch the current actual `Gas Ceiling` of a block.\r\n* If this feature dose not exists, we never know what `Gas Ceiling` value exactly.\r\n\r\nWhat are the use-cases?\r\n* There is an official documentation about [gas limit of block](https://ethereum.org/en/developers/docs/blocks/#block-size), but user or devs cannot knows what value exactly is set up in nodes. \r\n* I also saw [this tweet](https://twitter.com/etherchain_org/status/1273912037274537984?s=20), but cannot find the actual \"Gas Limit of block\" value in source codes or any place. And found that `GasCeiling` field. It is the actual `gas limit of block` value set on node. Please let me know if I'm missing something.\r\n* So if this API exists, user or devs can knows the actual `Gas Limit` of a Block by using API. \r\n\r\n# Implementation\r\n\r\nDo you have ideas regarding the implementation of this feature?\r\n* Returning `worker.config.GasCeil` (in `miner/miner.go`) would be ok just now. \r\n\r\nAre you willing to implement this feature?\r\n* Of course.",
