    "body": "@holiman \r\nHi. \r\nI'm not a node operator but, want to figure out the real [block gas limit](https://ethereum.org/en/developers/docs/blocks/#block-size) of Ethereum.\r\n\r\nI believe block gas limit matter because this is the indicator related with performance(or limitation?) of Ethereum.\r\n\r\nHigh block gas limit means it can include more txs than low block gas limit.\r\n\r\nIMHO, Researchers or developers who want to know the actual specifications of Ethereum are likely to be able to use this indicator.",
